<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Italy-Mafia     07-03 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Italy-Mafia,0114</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Link Double Slaying to Mafia Informant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In an apparent reprisal against the family
of a Mafia informant, gunmen killed two cousins as they sprayed a
car with pistol and shotgun fire, police reported.
   The victims of Monday's shooting were identified as Giorgio, 50,
and Salvatore Mandala, 32, cousins related to the wife of Totuccio
Contorno, a Mafioso who has turned state's evidence.
   The victims were construction workers.
   The were attacked as they were taking their lunch break in a
parked Fiat 128, police said. The killers sped away in their own
car, which was later found set afire about a half mile away.
</TEXT>
