<HEAD>Prison Guard Dies After Beating</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOLIET, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inmates beat to death a guard at a
maximum-security state prison, authorities said.
   The 2,108 inmates at Stateville Correctional Center were being
kept locked in the cells indefinitely today.
   Lawrence ``Frank'' Kush Jr., 24, of Chicago Heights, died at St.
Joseph Medical Center on Sunday night, a day after an unspecified
number of inmates beat him with a pipe, said Nic Howell, a state
corrections department spokesman.
   ``We are not to the point yet of specifically identifying who did
what,'' Howell said. ``But the investigation has turned up
indications of people who were involved.''
   The last time a Stateville prison employee was killed was in
October 1988, when a supply supervisor in the commissary was slain
by an inmate during an attempted robbery.
   The inmate is awaiting trial in the slaying.
