<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Manson-Bungalow     07-03 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Manson-Bungalow,0132</SECOND>
<HEAD>House Where Manson Followers Murdered Couple is Up For Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The bungalow where disciples of Charles Manson
murdered Rosemary and Leno La Bianca 20 years ago is for sale for
$599,000.
   Despite the price, the 1,655-square-foot house is so rundown that
Cliff Claycomb, one of the real estate agents listing the property,
called it a ``tear down.'' It has broken windows and its guest house
is a charred ruin.
   Since the LaBiancas were slain in 1969, the house, built in 1922
and remodeled in 1930, has been occupied mainly by renters.
   Another property made infamous by the Manson family, the house
above Benedict Canyon where actress Sharon Tate and four other
victims were murdered, reportedly sold in January for $2 million.
</TEXT>
