<FIRST>u i PM-Lebanon-Israel 1stLd-Writethru   07-03 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lebanon-Israel, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0514,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bomb Explodes Near Israeli Patrol; Lebanese Say Soldier Killed</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: Leads with 4 grafs to ADD Israeli denial of casualties. Pickup
4th pvs, `Israel carved...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TYRE, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A roadside bomb exploded today in south
Lebanon as an Israeli army patrol rolled by. One soldier was killed
and several were wounded, a security source said.
   An Israeli army spokesman confirmed the blast but denied there
were casualties.
   The security source, speaking in Tyre, 50 miles south of Beirut,
said the blast occurred about 1:30 p.m. in Israel's self-designated
``security zone'' as the convoy headed toward the village of Bint
Jbeil.
   The source, insisting on anonymity, said about 20 soldiers were
on a patrol mission in two armored personnel carriers and a jeep.
   Israel carved out the security zone when it withdrew the bulk of
its army from south Lebanon in the summer of 1985, three years after
it invaded its northern neighbor.
   The strip, which runs from the Mediterranean coast in the west to
the foothills of Mount Hermon in the east, is about six to 10 miles
deep. It serves as a buffer against border attacks.
</TEXT>
