<SECOND>PM-Afghan Defectors,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Afghan Air Force Officers Seek Asylum In Pakistan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUETTA, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Afghan air force officers flew a
government helicopter into Pakistan today and asked for political
asylum for their crew, the Defense Ministry said.
   A ministry spokesman said three majors and a captain were among
the crew. He did not give the number of defectors and said he had
few other details.
   The helicopter crossed the border and landed near the border city
of Chaman, 60 miles west of Quetta, in Pakistan's southwestern
province of Baluchistan, he said. He did not identify the type of
aircraft.
   Pakistan is headquarters for Moslem guerrillas fighting the
pro-Soviet government in Afghanistan.
