<FIRST>u a PM-Abortion-Fire     07-03 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Abortion-Fire,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Hampshire Abortion Clinic Fire Ruled Arson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire that damaged an abortion clinic hours
before today's U.S. Supreme Court abortion decision was arson, a
fire department official said.
   ``The case was incendiary, meaning it was intentionally set,''
said Capt. Jack Davis.
   Davis released no further details about the cause of the 2 a.m.
fire at the Feminist Health Center, but he said police were
investigating.
   The fire occurred at 2 a.m., eight hours before the U.S. Supreme
Court released a long-awaited ruling in a Missouri case
significantly curtailing the right of women to get legal abortions.
   ``The department is fully aware of the politics surrounding the
Feminist Health Center and the abortion issue,'' fire Capt. Scott
Chase said before the arson determination was confirmed.
   The fire, confined to a bookcase in one room in the unoccupied
building, was put out with a portable extinguisher, Chase said.
   The clinic had been a frequent target of picketing by abortion
protesters.
</TEXT>
