<HEAD>Boy Attacked by Wolf Held in Captivity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KENYON, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 5-year-old boy was in critical condition
Monday after a wolf held in captivity attacked him.
   Peter Lemke of Kenyon walked into Doug Earl's yard Saturday
morning, possibly to play with Earl's pet wolf, said police Officer
Troy Dunn. The boy was found semiconscious at about 11:30 a.m. with
the wolf standing over him, he said.
   The boy had multiple lacerations and punctures on the front and
back of his abdomen and on his legs and arms, Dunn said, and was
taken to St. Marys Hospital in Rochester.
   The wolf was temporarily quarantined, Dunn said.
   The Department of Natural Resources would intervene if it was
determined the wolf was taken from the wild said Nancy Hunder of the
DNR's enforcement division. If the owner shows a receipt that the
animal was taken from a private game farm, it is treated as a dog,
horse or any other domestic animal.
</TEXT>
