<HEAD>Postal Service Stops Delivery On `Crime-Infested' Street</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LYNN, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Postal Service temporarily suspended
home mail delivery on a street in this blue-collar Boston suburb
because it was too dangerous for carriers to enter the high-crime,
drug-infested area.
   ``Our first responsibility is to protect our letter carriers,''
said Lynn postal supervisor Richard Coppinger.
