assaulted when she delivered mail in a run-down apartment building.
Earlier this month, a letter carrier narrowly escaped injury when a
fight broke out between two occupants of an apartment building.
   Vine Street residents said they were angered by the decision to
end mail delivery to the entire street.
   ``It's very unfair for us,'' said Nathan Guy, 23. ``There are
only certain people responsible and they've made the whole street
suffer.''
