<HEAD>Fishermen Taken from Beached Trawler by Helicopter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Taiwanese fishing trawler
loaded with frozen squid ran aground Monday, but the crew was
rescued by a South African air force helicopter.
   The 340-ton Mengya 366, on its way home to Taiwan after leaving
Cape Town on Saturday, signaled it had run aground after hitting a
submerged object in rough waters less than a mile from the mouth of
the Tsitsikamma River in southern South Africa.
   The accident site, west of Cape St. Francis, is known for its
rugged coastline.
   The air force helicopter plucked the crewmen from the vessel and
flew them to the beach, according to the South African Broadcasting
Corp. They were later transported by police to the town of
Humansdorp.
