<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Deficit     07-03 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Deficit,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>China Had $2.1 Billion Deficit in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China last year registered a deficit of $2.1
billion, down slightly from earlier estimates, Finance Minister Wang
Bingqian said Monday.
   Wang told the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress that final calculations put China's revenues in 1988 at $71
billion and its expenditures at $73.1 billion.
   In March, Wang had estimated the deficit at $2.16 billion, about
the same as China's 1987 deficit. The nation's deficit in 1986 was
about $1.89 billion. That was low by international standards,
representing only 3.4 percent of state revenue and 0.75 percent of
the gross national product.
   China's largest deficit was in 1979, when expenditures outweighed
revenues by $4.86 billion.
   Wang said $17 billion was appropriated for capital construction
last year. State investment in agricultural production and cultural,
scientific and health projects increased considerably last year, he
added, but did not give any figures.
</TEXT>
