<FIRST>r a AM-Bush-Text     07-03 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bush-Text,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Text of President's Statement on Abortion Ruling</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Scotus-Abortion, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KENNEBUNKPORT, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is a transcript of
President Bush's written statement in reaction to Monday's Supreme
Court decision restoring state powers to regulate abortion:
   We welcome this decision. By upholding the Missouri statute, the
court appears to have begun to restore to the people the ability to
protect the unborn. We continue to believe that Roe vs. Wade was
incorrectly decided, and should be reviewed.
   Americans obviously differ over the difficult issue underlying
this case _ the morality and appropriate legal status of abortion.
Any decision in this area will stir strong feelings. Nevertheless, I
have confidence that the American people will continue to express
their deeply held convictions on this subject within the bounds of
civility and our legal institutions.
</TEXT>
