<FILEID>AP-NR-07-03-89 2128EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-SpaceShuttle     07-03 0308</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Space Shuttle,0315</SECOND>
<HEAD>Columbia Closer to Launch Pad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Space shuttle Columbia, fresh out of
a three-year remodeling job, was rolled closer to the launch pad
Monday for final touches before carrying a secret Pentagon payload
into space.
   The National Aeronautics and Space Administration is hoping for a
July 31 launch, but some space agency officials believe liftoff will
be delayed until early August because flight preparations have taken
longer than expected.
   Columbia last flew Jan. 10, 1986, the last mission before sister
ship Challenger exploded and the shuttle fleet was grounded.
   In another development Monday, investigators confirmed reports
that a bad turbopump bearing caused a shuttle engine to shut down
prematurely and catch fire during a June 23 test at NASA's Stennis
Space Center in Bay St. Louis, Miss.
   The incident is not expected to affect Columbia's launch because
the test involved a developmental engine, not flight hardware, said
Armis L. Worlund, chief investigator for a team of experts at the
Rocketdyne Division of shuttle maker Rockwell International Corp. in
Canoga Park, Calif., which dismantled and inspected the engine last
weekend.
   The turbopump circulates liquid oxygen through the shuttle's fuel
lines before launch, keeping them ready for main engine ignition.
NASA has had trouble with other turbopumps before. One carrying
liquid hydrogen shorted out during a launch countdown last April,
forcing a one-week delay in the flight of shuttle Atlantis.
   At the cape, workers, joined by four of the five astronauts who
will fly Columbia, towed America's oldest orbiter into the huge
assembly building at dawn Monday.
   Columbia, a source of spare parts for sister ships since 1986,
will be hoisted into a nose-up position and mated with its fuel tank
and twin booster rockets. Final preparations for the trip to the
launch pad are expected to take seven to 10 days.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
