<FIRST>r i AM-Panama-ShipCollision     07-03 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Panama-Ship Collision,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Ships Collide in Panama Canal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two ships collided in the Panama Canal
on Monday, injuring four people aboard a tug but not disrupting
traffic in the canal, the Panama Canal Commission said in a
communique.
   It said the Philippine ship Ballena changed direction suddenly
while moving north in the Miraflores Locks and struck the Vojvodina,
a Yugoslav-registered vessel that was headed south.
   A tug helping the Ballena was trapped between the two vessels.
Four tug crew members were treated for injuries at a hospital and
released, the communique said.
   A hold in the Vojvodina was ripped open, while the Ballena
suffered minor damage, the commission said.
</TEXT>
