<FIRST>r f PM-Poll-Method     07-03 0642</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poll-Method,0665</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-Movies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This Media General-Associated Press poll is based
on telephone interviews May 5-13 with 1,084 adults in the
continental United States.
   Phone numbers were selected randomly and interviews were
conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday, a random
phenomenon.
   The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample.
The poll has a 3-point margin of error, meaning that 19 of 20 times
its findings should be within 3 points of the result if every adult
American were asked the same questions. The error margin is larger
for subgroups; it is 4 points for women and 6 points for the 18-29
age group, for example.
   There are other sources of potential error in polls, including
the wording and order of questions. These are the questions in this
poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100:
   1. When was the last time you went out to see a movie _ was it
within the past week, within the past month, within the past three
months, or was it longer ago that that? Week: 10 percent. Month: 19.
Three months: 17. Longer: 54. Never: 1. Don't know or no answer: 0.
   2. About how many times did you go out to the movies within the
past 12 months? None: 35 percent. 1 to 4: 38 percent. 5 to 10: 14
percent. 11 to 20: 8 percent. 21 to 30: 3 percent. 31 to 40: 1
percent. 41 to 50: 1 percent. Over 50: 1 percent. DK-NA: 1 percent.
   3. How would you rate the last movie you went out to see _
excellent, good, only fair or poor? Excellent: 29. Good: 35. Fair:
15. Poor: 7. DK-NA: 15.
   4. And what's your overall impression of the movies nowadays _
would you rate them excellent, good, only fair or poor? Excellent:
3. Good: 31. Fair: 34. Poor: 27. DK-NA: 4.
   5a. If you hear a movie has violence in it, would that make you
more likely to go see it, less likely, or wouldn't it matter? More:
3. Less: 60. Wouldn't matter: 35. DK-NA: 1.
   b. ... profanity? More: 2. Less: 57. Wouldn't matter: 40. DK-NA:
1.
   c. ... nudity? More: 4. Less: 57. Wouldn't matter: 38. DK-NA: 1.
   6a. Overall, do most movies that come out nowadays have too much
violence in them, or not? Yes: 82. No: 14. DK-NA: 4.
   b. ... profanity? Yes: 80. No: 16. DK-NA: 4.
   c. ... nudity? Yes: 72. No: 22. DK-NA: 5.
   7. Would you say the overall quality of movies has been getting
better over the years, getting worse, or hasn't there been much
change? Better: 17. Worse: 56. Unchanged: 24. DK-NA: 3.
   8a. How much was the admission at the last movie you went out to
see? Less than $1: 1. $1-$3: 30. $4: 21. $5: 22. $6: 8. $7 or more:
2. Never been: 1. DK-NA: 16.
   b. Do you think that's reasonable? Yes: 54. No: 45. DK-NA: 1.
   9. Do you happen to own a VCR, that is, a videocassette recorder?
Yes: 75. No: 25. DK-NA: 1.
   10. (If yes) When was the last time you rented a movie to watch
on the VCR _ was it within the past week, within the past month,
within the past three months, or was it longer ago than that? Week:
45. Month: 24. Three months: 11. Longer: 14. Never: 6. DK-NA: 0.
   11. About how many times did you rent a movie to watch on the VCR
in the past 12 months? None: 5. 1-4: 12. 5-10: 14. 11-20: 19. 21-30:
14. 31-40: 5. 41-50: 6. Over 50: 24. DK-NA: 1.
   12. Since you got the VCR, have you been going out to the movies
less often, more often, or about the same amount? Less: 50. More: 1.
Same: 47. DK-NA: 2.
</TEXT>
