<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Stocks     07-03 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Firmer but Off Highs at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were stronger but off earlier peaks at
midday Monday as the release of final British sales figures for May
trimmed the market's advance, dealers said.
   Retail sales volume rose a revised 3.0 percent in May from April,
the Department of Trade and Industry said and was the highest since
April 1987 when the index rose 3.1 percent.
   Dealers said the market hardened from the outset, as some fresh
new buying emerged on the first day of the new account period and
the third quarter.
   But many traders weren't expected to enter the market until later
in the week.
   At about noon in London, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index was up 11.5 points, or 0.5 percent, at 2,162.5, off
its late morning best of 2,167.0. The index began at its minimum
level of 2,154.9, a gain of just 3.9 points.
   Volume at midday was 258.5 million shares compared with 256.1
million shares at the same time Friday.
</TEXT>
