<FIRST>r f PM-Chesebrough-Minnetonka 1stLd-Writethru   07-03 0366</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Chesebrough-Minnetonka, 1st Ld-Writethru,0376</SECOND>
<HEAD>Unilever Division To Acquire Calvin Klein Cosmetics Owner for $376
Million</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: RECASTS lead to correct spelling of Obsession and delete day
to conform to PM style; CORRECTS share price in 6th graf to $22.86; minor
editing throughout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chesebrough-Ponds Inc. has agreed to pay $376
million for Minnetonka Corp., the maker of Calvin Klein personal
care items and fragrances including Obsession perfume, the companies
said.
   New York-based Unilever United States Inc., the parent company of
Chesebrough-Ponds, said Sunday it simultaneously is selling two
Minnetonka divisions to a Japanese-owned company for about $70
million.
   The deal gives Chesebrough-Ponds all products made by
Bloomington, Minn.-based Minnetonka's Calvin Klein Cosmetics Corp.,
including the fragrances Obsession, Obsession for Men, Eternity and
Calvin.
   It also adds to the burgeoning personal care empire of Unilever,
the giant European conglomerate that owns Unilever United States and
had 1988 sales of $31 billion.
   Calvin Klein Cosmetics also is used on leather accessories such
as handbags and belts. Calvin Klein Cosmetics had 1988 net sales of
$158 million, about 82 percent in the United States.
   The $22.86-a-share deal for all of Minnetonka's outstanding
shares values Calvin Klein Cosmetics at about $306 million.
Minnetonka closed Friday at $25-a-share in national over-the-counter
trading.
   ``After meeting with the management of Unilever, I feel we can
share the same goals for the growth of our business,'' Klein said in
a statement. ``We look forward to a long and productive
relationship.''
   As part of the deal, Minnetonka has agreed to sell its Fragrance
Marketing Group and Minnetonka Medical divisions and the Minnetonka
name for $70 million to Tsumura International Inc., the U.S.
subsidiary of Tsumura &amp; Co. of Japan. The subsidiary markets
cosmetics and toiletries in the United States.
   ``We are ... very pleased that the employees of our various
operating (companies) united will be joining well-regarded companies
that can continue the growth of these businesses and brands,''
Minnetonka Chairman Robert R. Taylor said.
   Unilever United States is the holding company for the U.S.
businesses owned by Anglo-Dutch Unilever, the maker of food,
detergent and personal care items.
   Unilever already owns fragrances including Elizabeth Taylor's
Passion, Cerruti, Scherrer and White Shoulders.
</TEXT>
