<FIRST>r f BC-Obit-Linen     07-03 0150</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Obit-Linen,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Media General Executive Dies In London</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James A. Linen IV, executive vice president
of Media General Inc. and head of the Richmond-based company's
broadcast operations, died in London from injuries suffered in a
jogging accident.
   Linen, 51, died early Sunday in Westminster Hospital, officials
said.
   Linen, vacationing in London for the Wimbledon tennis
championships, was hit by a van in a pedestrian crosswalk as he was
jogging Wednesday. Authorities said Linen suffered multiple
fractures and massive internal injuries, and that he died from
pulmonary dysfunction.
   A native of Scranton, Pa., and a 1960 graduate of Yale
University, Linen joined Media General, which publishes the Richmond
Times-Dispatch and The Richmond News Leader, in October 1977 as a
vice president.
   He was promoted to senior vice president in 1981, and four years
later was made executive vice president in charge of Media General's
broadcast operations.
</TEXT>
